            <h2 data-i18n="guide_modal_title_4">Relative Rotation</h2>
            <p data-i18n-html="guide_modal_body_4">Sectors plotted on two axes: <strong>relative strength</strong> vs. benchmark (x) and whether that strength is <strong>accelerating</strong> (y). Sectors rotate counter-clockwise through four quadrants:</p>
            <ul data-i18n-html="guide_modal_list_4">
              <li><span class="signal-hi">Leading</span> (top-right) &mdash; outperforming and accelerating</li>
              <li><span class="signal-lo">Weakening</span> (bottom-right) &mdash; outperforming but decelerating</li>
              <li><strong>Lagging</strong> (bottom-left) &mdash; underperforming and decelerating</li>
              <li><span class="signal-hi">Improving</span> (top-left) &mdash; the entry zone</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="guide-tip" data-i18n-html="guide_modal_tip_4"><strong>Key:</strong> Buy in Improving before the move to Leading. Sell in Weakening before the drop to Lagging. The dotted tail shows the last 3 scans &mdash; direction matters more than position.</div>
          </div>
        </article>

